  "source": "Pathology_Robbins_textbook_data.txt: Scabies is caused by the mite Sarcoptes scabiei var. hominis. The impregnated female burrows into the stratum corneum, depositing eggs and feces as it creates a tunnel. The infestation produces an intensely pruritic eruption caused by sensitization to the mite and its products. The lesions consist of small, erythematous, excoriated papules and vesicles, with characteristic distribution in the interdigital spaces, flexor aspects of wrists, axillae, periumbilical skin, and genitalia. Definitive diagnosis is established by microscopic demonstration of mites, eggs, or feces in scrapings from lesions. Permethrin 5% cream is the treatment of choice for scabies.",
